<subSubSection pageId="93" pageNumber="577" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="93.[2017,2612,1680,2108]" lastBlockId="93.[1403,2610,2114,3487]" pageId="93" pageNumber="577">
<taxonomicName box="[2017,2218,1803,1832]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="577" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="turpis">Artibeus turpis</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[2333,2444,1803,1832]" country="Mexico" name="Tabasco" pageId="93" pageNumber="577">Tabasco</collectingRegion>
(southern 
<collectingCountry box="[2017,2126,1846,1871]" name="Mexico" pageId="93" pageNumber="577">Mexico</collectingCountry>
), described by RK. Andersen in 1906, 1s a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[2426,2603,1882,1911]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Dermanura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="577" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="phaeotis">A. p. phaeotis</taxonomicName>
. Considered in the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[2412,2559,1917,1950]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Dermanura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="577" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Dermanura</taxonomicName>
by some authors but reassigned to 
<taxonomicName box="[2505,2611,1956,1989]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="577" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Artibeus</taxonomicName>
(subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[2176,2324,2000,2029]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Dermanura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="577" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Dermanura</taxonomicName>
) after reinterpretation of molecular results. Some authors recognized A. ravus as a synonym of A. 
<taxonomicName box="[1441,1545,2114,2147]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Dermanura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="577" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="phaeotis">phaeotis</taxonomicName>
, but according to molecular evidence, they are considered different species. Three subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
